Wound dressing has been used for decades to be effective for accelerating skin 
wound healing. However, practical applications are still limited due to their 
lower cell affinity, tissue adhesiveness, and biocompatibility. Natural polymers 
are the important biomaterials because of their excellent biodegradability, 
biocompatibility, and low immunogenicity. In this work, the composite 
bioadhesives (PLS-CS/RSF) were prepared from regenerated silk fibroin (RSF) and 
polylysine-modified chitosan (PLS-CS) that were cross-linked by Ca2+ ions. The 
